Interface Hierarchical<T>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<T>

    public interface Hierarchical<T>
extends java.lang.Iterable<T>
    an interface that defines hierarchical data structures with a parent-child relationship. It is an extension of the Iterable interface which provides access to the children of a hierarchical element.
